<FIRST>r a AM-People-Brubeck     02-07 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Brubeck,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jazz Pianist Dave Brubeck Has Successful Heart Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jazz pianist Dave Brubeck underwent
successful triple-bypass heart surgery Tuesday at Yale-New Haven
Hospital, officials said.
   Brubeck, 68, underwent 4{ hours of surgery and was listed in
critical but stable condition in the intensive care unit, hospital
spokeswoman Cathy Zaorski said.
   Doctors had been watching Brubeck's problems with clogged
arteries for about eight years, but decided only recently that he
should undergo surgery, Brubeck's manager Russell Gloyd said.
   Brubeck, who lives in Wilton, plans to resume limited travel and
performances in a couple of months, Gloyd said.
   Zaorski said Brubeck would remain in the hospital for a week to
10 days.
   Gloyd said he was unsure when Brubeck would be able to perform
again.
   ``We're looking at that right now. It's all going to depend on
his recovery. We're hoping that within two to three months he can
begin a limited performance schedule.''
</TEXT>
