<FIRST>r a BC-GospelMusic     02-07 0321</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Gospel Music,0333</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sandi Patti Leads Finalists</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOE EDWARDS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Singer Sandi Patti was chosen a finalist
Tuesday as the Gospel Music Association's artist of the year and No.
1 female vocalist.
   Amy Grant, whose music has crossed over to the pop charts, joins
her as a finalist in both categories.
   Other finalists for artist of the year, the top award, are the
brother-sister duet Bebe and Cece Winans, Carman and Steve Green.
   Joining Patti and Grant as finalists for No. 1 female vocalist
are Cece Winans, Margaret Becker and Twila Paris.
   Larnelle Harris, male vocalist of the year in 1988, leads the
finalists for the 1989 honor. Others are Bebe Winans, Carman, Green
and Wayne Watson.
   Winners of the 20th annual awards will be announced during a gala
at the Tennessee Performing Arts Center April 13 during Gospel Music
Week.
   Patti, of Anderson, Ind., has been voted top female vocalist for
seven straight years. She has been voted Christian music's No. 1
artist five times, including the past two years.
   Since 1984, she has won four Grammy awards.
   Last month she performed as part of the inauguration ceremonies
for President Bush.
   Harris, like Miss Patti, has won four Grammy awards. He also is
known for his performances at Billy Graham crusades.
   Grant, of Nashville, joined with ex-Chicago lead singer Peter
Cetera on a No. 1 pop hit, ``Next Time I Fall,'' in 1986. Her
``Unguarded'' and ``Age to Age'' gospel-pop albums have sold more
than 1 million copies apiece.
   Finalists and winners are chosen by the singers, musicians,
songwriters and others in the Nashville-based gospel association,
which has 3,000 members.
   The awards are called the Dove Awards in honor of the bird that
appeared in the biblical account of the baptism of Jesus.
   Harris, of Louisville, Ky., was male vocalist of the year in 1986
and 1983 in addition to last year.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
