<HEAD>With BC-Gospel Music</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are finalists for the 20th annual
Gospel Music Association awards:
   Artist of the Year: Amy Grant; Bebe and Cece Winans; Carman;
Sandi Patti; Steve Grant.
   Male Vocalist of the Year: Bebe Winans; Carman; Larnelle Harris;
Steve Green; Wayne Watson.
   Female Vocalist of the Year: Amy Grant; Cece Winans; Margaret
Becker; Sandi Patti; Twila Paris.
   Songwriter of the Year: Larnelle Harris; Phil McHugh; Ray Boltz;
Steven Curtis Chapman; Wayne Watson.
   Group of the Year: Bebe &amp; Cece Winans; First Call; Mylon and
Broken Heart; Petra; Take 6.
   New Artist of the Year: Billy and Sarah Gaines; Bruce Carroll;
Geoff Moore; Kim Boyce; Kim Hill; Take 6 (six finalists due to tie
in voting).
   Metal Recorded Song of the Year: ``Breakaway,'' Rosanna's
Raiders; ``Dancing On The Head Of The Serpent,'' Jerusalem; ``Enough
Is Enough,'' Whitecross; ``In God We Trust,'' Stryper; ``Shout,
Shout,'' Ken Tamplin.
   Rock Recorded Song of the Year: ``A Place To Stand,'' Geoff Moore
&amp; The Distance; ``All Right,'' Amy Grant; ``Light In The Darkness,''
Margaret Becker; ``Rock Solid,'' Degarmo & Key; ``Won By One,''
Mylong &amp; Broken Heart.
   Contemporary Recorded Song of the Year: ``Awesome God,'' Rich
Mullins; ``Find Me,'' Margaret Becker; ``Lead Me On,'' Any Grant;
``Radically Saved,'' Carman.
   Inspirational Recorded Song of the Year: ``Daystar (Shine Down On
Me),'' Gaither Vocal Band; ``Find Us Faithful,'' Steve Green; ``In
Heaven's Eyes,'' Sandi Patti; ``Love Will Be Our Home,'' Sandi
Patti; ``Thank You,'' Ray Boltz.
   Southern Gospel Recorded Song of the Year: ``Champion Of Love,''
The Cathedrals; ``Daystar (Shine Down On Me),'' Cathedral Quartet;
``For Every Generation,'' The Talleys; ``God On The Mountain,'' The
McKameys; ``We Are Still The Church,'' The Talleys.
   Country Recorded Song of the Year: ``Above And Beyond,'' Bruce
Carroll; ``Doin' It By The Book,'' The Whites; ``God's Own Lamb,''
Buddy Greene; ``Heaven Knows,'' Kelly Nelon Thompson; ``Mount Up
With Wings,'' Dallas Holm.
   Contemporary Black Gospel Recorded Song of the Year: ``Hold Up
The Light,'' New Jersey Mass Choir; ``If We Ever,'' Take 6; ``Mary,
Don't You Weep,'' Take 6; ``The Might &amp; The Majesty,'' Morris
Chapman; ``Vision,'' The Richard Smallwood Singers.
   Traditional Black Gospel Recorded Song of the Year: ``Higher
Ground,'' Vernessa Mitchell; ``Hold My Mule,'' Shirley Caesar;
``Pass Me Not; Voices Of Light,'' Fanny Crosby; ``We're All In The
Same Boat,'' Tramine Hawkins; ``What Shall I Do?,'' Tramine Hawkins.
