<DATELINE>SALEM, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An evangelist who admitted molesting at least
100 boys along the Southern revival circuit since the 1960s was
sentenced to 2{ years in prison today for sodomizing two teen-agers.
   ``I suppose the thing that troubles me most is somebody of the
cloth, who knows the truth, has openly and flagrantly lied,'' Judge
Kenneth Trabue told Mario ``Tony'' Leyva. ``There was an overt
effort to poison the jury on your behalf.''
   Leyva, a 43-year-old Pentecostal preacher from Columbus, Ga.,
testified at his trial in state court in September that he never had
sex with children, but he later told the FBI he had sexually abused
at least 100 boys beginning in the 1960s.
