<FIRST>d a PM-Bison-Fatal     02-07 0168</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Bison-Fatal,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snowmobiler Killed In Collision With Bison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK, Wyo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A snowmobiler was killed
in a collision with a bison, park officials said today.
   Donald M. Anderson, 48, of Geraldine, Mont., died at a hospital
Monday night shortly after the accident, which occurred while he was
snowmobiling with several friends after dark, said park spokeswoman
Joan Anzelmo.
   Anderson's friends drove ahead and lost sight of him, she said.
They went back to find him severely injured on the ground, clumps of
bison hair nearby, Anzelmo said.
   ``It seems that he just ran into a bison on the road. Bison due
frequent that road and it's hard to see them at night,'' said
Anzelmo. ``Apparently this group had passed two other groups of
bison.''
   Anzelmo said rangers would keep watch for the bison but that the
animal may have walked away unharmed. Anzelmo said it was the first
incident she could recall in which a snowmobiler was killed in a
collision with an animal.
</TEXT>
