<BYLINE>By DONNA CASSATA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ranking Republican on the Senate Armed
Services Committee said today an FBI report on new allegations
against Defense Secretary-designate John Tower ``does not provide a
basis for any disqualification.''
   Sen. John Warner, R-Va., told reporters that he was briefed by
the White House on the report, which sources ed on
new charges of drinking and womanizing, and he later briehave said centerfed
the GOP
members of the committee.
   ``The preliminary report of the investigation which Senator (Sam)
Nunn and I requested on Thursday has been made available,'' Warner
said. ``It provides, at the judgment of White House counsel, no
basis on which senators could find the factual situation that would
amount to any disqualification.''
   At the White House, press secretary Marlin Fitzwater said that
``our understanding is the FBI is close to concluding their reports
and they have found no difficulties or problems that haven't been
resolved.''
