   ``I think people would not want a person to step aside, given
rumor, particularly if the rumor is baseless,'' the president said.
``And the problem is the process is taking a little longer than I
would like, and yet, I think the Senate has got to do what they're
doing _ looking at these allegations very carefully.''
   Bush added, however, that if any rumors or innuendoes turned out
to be ``a substantive allegation of this nature, of course it would
concern me.''
