Tuesday he wants to conquer Mount Everest again, this time by
floating over the world's highest peak in a hot-air balloon.
   ``I would not ever dream of struggling up Mount Everest again.
Once is quite enough,'' he told reporters. But ``the thought of
wafting across that mountain in a balloon is superb.''
   Bonnington, 54, who climbed 29,029-foot Mount Everest in 1985,
