<HEAD>Fire Breaks Out At High School</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SHADYSIDE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A student is suspected of starting a fire
that caused extensive damage to a utility room at a high school
Tuesday, but no one was injured, authorities said.
   The fire at Shadyside High School in this eastern Ohio city was
reported at 2:55 p.m., about the time students were leaving for the
day, firefighter Norman Davis said. The blaze was contained about 1{
hours later, he said.
   Teachers spread word of the fire from classroom to classroom and
the school's approximately 270 students escaped before smoke was
visible in the main building, authorities said. No injuries were
reported.
   A juvenile who is a student at the school is suspected of setting
the blaze, said Shadyside police Chief Mike Valloric. Police would
not release the boy's age and turned the case over to prosecutors.
   Fire damage was confined to the utility room, although
firefighters also opened two holes in the gymnasium roof,
Superintendent Robert Henry said.
