<TEXT>
   Share prices firmed and volume accelerated at
midday Tuesday, shrugging off a weak start, traders said.
   The recovery was due partly to the futures market, where the
March Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index showed an
18-point advance on its Monday close, and on strong buying in
chemical, pharmaceutical and other dollar-earning stocks, traders
said.
   However, they said they remained unconvinced that the market has
fully shaken the profit-taking pressure which sent the index
tumbling 25.6 points Monday.
