<HEAD>GM Recalls Cars For Potential Fuel Leaks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp. on Tuesday recalled 16,800
compact and midsize 1989 cars because of a potential fuel leak.
   GM said it wasn't aware of the problems occurring in cars on the
road.
   The company recalled Chevrolet Cavalier, Corsica and Beretta,
Pontiac Sunbird and Buick Skyhawk compact cars and Pontiac Grand
Prix and Buick Regal midsize models.
   The company said pressure changes in the cars' fuel tanks could
cause small cracks and leaks.
   Dealers have been told to inspect and replace the tanks if
necessary without charge to the owner.
