<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-GTE     02-07 0248</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-GTE,0256</SECOND>
<HEAD>GE Yearly Earnings Up Nine Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Corp. on Tuesday said fourth-quarter
earnings for 1988 were down 2 percent from the same period the
previous year, when the telecommunications company benefited from a
property sale that boosted net income for the quarter by $26 million.
   The company reported fourth-quarter net income of $326 million,
or 96 cents a share, on consolidated revenues and sales of $4.3
billion, compared to net income of $334 million, or 99 cents a
share, on consolidated revenues of $4.1 billion for the same period
a year ago.
   Excluding non-operating items, quarterly profits would have risen
6 percent, GTE said.
   For the full year, net income rose 9 percent to a record-high
$1.2 billion, compared to $1.1 billion earned in 1987. Earnings per
share totaled $3.58, also up 9 percent over the $3.29 reported a
year ago. Consolidated 1988 revenues and sales were $16.5 billion, 7
percent more than the $15.4 billion reported for 1987.
   James L. Johnson, GTE chairman and chief executive, noted that
the price of GTE stock rose by 26 percent in 1988 and said the
company has taken several steps to enhance future earnings growth.
   ``These included reducing our holdings in US Sprint and in our
network-switching business, divesting certain other businesses not
earning an adequate return as wellin a prepared statement.
